  "text": "NSAIDs could reduce the risk of cancer through the inhibition of cyclooxygenase-2 (COX-2) [CITATION_1] , the enzyme that is responsible for the production of various prostaglandins. Prostaglandins play a key role on the accelerated proliferation of tumor tissue. Furthermore there is mounting evidence that NSAIDs may have the ability to restore apoptosis and inhibit angiogenesis [CITATION_2] .",
